 former top-level 'arm' is removed; config.arm is the only arm declaration), and native --supersedes/--reason flags for the retry path. (4) G1/G2/G4 counts hardening in both scorers: per-family control acceptable ('ok') sums must equal the run-level n_control_refused_acceptable; run-level totals n_covered/n_control/dev_n, dev_parse_refused, and every gold-replication counter must be strict non-negative integers; dev_parse_refused <= dev_n; G4 divides only well-formed in-range counters. (5) Honesty corrections carried in the same change: the instrument docstring no longer claims a byte-identical engine (G2 behavioural claim restated), and the section-14.8 item-7 'bit-equal' complement claim is softened to the measured fact (identical gate decision at every integer count; 4/527 differs by one binary64 ULP, 9/855 bit-equal). All edits are log-schema/log-writer/scorer/instrument-envelope side; no phrasing or eval byte, endpoint, threshold, decision boundary, or planned n moves.", "backing_ref": "docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md section 14.9; poc/nlb-skeptic/skeptic-round2-output.txt sha256 6e60f408a4231c595832dd6b91262ef49c3617a410e5e71522ea33bb578b7773 (attacks on the dict-valued and cross-arm supersedes, zeroed control-family ok, float totals and dev_parse_refused reproduced there); analysis/l3a_parse.py + analysis/a5_nl.py --selftest fixtures on each reproduced attack; scratch-log run-to-log integration demonstration via the real tools/registry/log-append.py", "rationale": "The round-2 re-audit proved the registered recovery path could not exist in a real hash-chained log (kot-log/1 additionalProperties:false rejects the field; log-append's supersede event cannot target ok rows; only ok rows reach the scorer), so freezing would have pinned an unexecutable protocol where one accidental duplicate append poisons the record permanently. Making the channel real in schema+writer+scorer, with append-time AND read-time enforcement of one registered rule, converts the promise into an executable, auditable mechanism while PRESERVING the anti-re-roll invariant (a successful row is only ever replaced by an explicit, reasoned, same-arm successor in the chain). The counts hardening closes the reproduced acceptance of contradictory control-family classifications and non-integral counters. Revisit condition: any change to kot-log/1 row identity or to canonical JSON serialization must re-derive the scorer's self-contained _row_sha twin.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10"}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:185:{"id": "ASM-0625", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "NLB skeptic round-3 remediation (extends the ASM-0621/ASM-0624 lawful edit set by exactly this named, diff-scoped edit set and no other; design doc 14.10 items A+B): (1) G0 COMPLETED - both pinned scorers re-validate the FULL append-time retry-supersession semantics that are order-independently checkable at read time: a run row carrying supersedes must state a non-blank string reason (missing_reason detail), and no target may be retired twice, the order-free form of log-append's not-already-superseded rule (retired_twice detail); both INSTRUMENT-INVALID in every log order. The registered 'two independent enforcements of one registered rule' defence-in-depth claim is thereby made TRUE rather than downgraded (resolution (a) of the round-3 finding-1 options). Target event/exit/phase remain enforced TRANSITIVELY and are registered as such: verdict-gen's eligibility filter drops non-run/non-final/non-ok rows before the scorer, leaving any reference to them dangling (already G0-invalid). (2) G1 SHORT-CIRCUIT - any g1_counts failure returns immediately after the gate block with instrument_valid false, an EMPTY analysis block, valid-JSON stdout and exit 0, so verdict-gen's frozen rule 0 fires the registered INSTRUMENT-INVALID and no rejected denominator (boolean/float/negative/missing) ever reaches Wilson/Holm/descriptive arithmetic (previously n_control=True crashed both scorers into ERR_P2_ANALYSIS and a5 n_covered=True emitted unserializable complex Wilson values). (3) G1 additionally types every remaining analysis-divided counter (label_strata, synonym-probe counters, frontend_total_ns when present; in-range non-negative integers, bool excluded) and non-dict metrics/pins_observed bodies on any arm are handled fail-closed, never as exceptions. (4) Fixture-side only: Holm-boundary fixtures now construct an internally consistent control split (non-acceptable remainder deducted from by_family ok). All edits are scorer-side; no phrasing or eval byte, instrument sha, endpoint, threshold, decision boundary, or planned n moves.", "backing_ref": "docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md section 14.10; poc/nlb-skeptic/skeptic-round3-output.txt sha256 5d1867482fab9065233936d8080b36b251116040cea93707f57604c922babdde (missing/blank-reason and double-retirement acceptance plus the boolean-total crash paths reproduced there); analysis/l3a_parse.py sha256 d6b3e65e6206cd781713f54c529c4b70bf6e72141e741704011f341a80901ce6 + analysis/a5_nl.py sha256 4ea2383cc8c75c8d32a50c8229fe13550a478847906f80ddb07e9d0827cde018 --selftest fixtures on each reproduced attack", "rationale": "The round-3 re-audit proved two claim-vs-implementation gaps inside already-registered items: the scorer-side defence-in-depth claim of ASM-0624 item (2) enumerated fewer checks than the append path enforces (an overclaim reachable from a manually constructed, schema-valid chain), and the ASM-0624 item (4) counts promise classified malformed counts INSTRUMENT-INVALID only when the scorer survived to say so (boolean denominators crashed it into ERR_P2_ANALYSIS instead). Making the scorer re-validate reason + single-retirement makes the registered independence claim true at trivial cost; short-circuiting on G1 failure makes the registered verdict classification mechanically reachable on every malformed-count input. Revisit condition: any change to kot-log/1 supersession semantics or to the analysis-consumed metric surface must update G0/G1 in both scorers in the same change.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10"}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:193:{"id": "ASM-0740", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "g3-llmproxy-v3 section-6 blinding-scan scope amendment (the ratified truthstyle-2x2 Amendment-A1 rule, ASM-0660, reused in its exact form): on the two HARNESS-CAPTURED surfaces events.jsonl and stderr.log - NEVER on user-prompt.txt - a case-insensitive blind-token match (kernel/nsm/necessity/sufficiency/hypothesis) is excluded from being a HIT iff, in the original pre-lowercase bytes, it lies wholly inside the base62 TAIL of a maximal Anthropic-format vendor identifier literal (req|msg)_[0-9A-Za-z]{20,48} with lowercase-exact prefix and non-word-adjacent boundaries (runs longer than 48 fail maximality - fail-closed); uniform over all five tokens; every byte outside qualifying tails scans byte-identically to the superseded v2 contract; ADDITIONALLY the section-5 RAW answer string (judge-emitted bytes) is re-scanned with ZERO exclusions (answer-surface strictness), so a real leak in item bytes or judge-emitted answer text still ABORTS. Reference implementation blinding_scan/_vendor_id_tail_spans/answer_blinding_hit in the pinned analysis/g3_llmproxy_v3.py (adapted from the A1 section-9.5 normative code; no g3 token is hex-embeddable, so the truthstyle hex-run branch has no analogue); the runner imports it, never reimplements; the section-8 preflight selftest proves the EXACT v2-abort bytes excluded and real-leak shapes still aborting. Motivation (measured): the v2 run 20260710T204828Z aborted on pass-A item g3-friend-07 when the pinned v2 whole-file grep hit nsM inside the harness-stamped request_id req_011Ccu3G1KQZ8ciX3SvEfnsM at events.jsonl offset 2242 - user-prompt clean, stderr empty, answer clean, judge never saw the token; every captured judge-pB attempt carries exactly two such 24-char-tail ids (judge-pA/codex: zero), so a perfectly blind 430-call judge-pB run expects ~0.6 coincidental nsm hits and the unamended scan aborts a clean run with probability ~0.5 under the null - a control firing on vendor machinery under the null detects nothing.", "backing_ref": "registry/corrections/truthstyle-2x2/4-blinding-audit-amendment-a1.json (ratified A1 rule, ASM-0660); poc/truthstyle-2x2/blinding-audit-clarification.md section 9; poc/g3-llmproxy-v2/opus-runs/20260710T204828Z/judge-pB-haiku45/run-log.txt and passA/g3-friend-07/c1_t0/events.jsonl (the measured false positive); analysis/g3_llmproxy_v3.py --selftest (fixtures incl. the verbatim abort-byte slice)", "rationale": "Base62 vendor-id tails can spell any pinned token by arithmetic coincidence (the A1 section-9.2 argument, byte-for-byte the same channel: two ids per captured judge-pB call, 22 windows x (2/62)^3 per id), so the unamended predicate fires with ~coin-flip probability per clean run and has no discriminative power on this channel; the exclusion is format-anchored, maximality-checked, fail-closed and surface-restricted, so item contamination and judge echoes fire byte-identically to v2, and the added zero-exclusion answer-surface scan closes the residual-risk shape A1 section-9.6 could only disclose, at zero false-positive cost (the valid answer grammar contains no base62 ids). Amending the scan scope preserves the control; scrubbing provenance or dropping surfaces would not.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "any v3-scan hit at run time is a boundary stop back to Fable (never a runner improvisation); any future vendor id format outside the (req|msg)_ 20-48-base62 shape that coincidentally spells a token will abort again and is its own boundary stop"}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:215:{"id": "ASM-0814", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "NL-boundary DEPENDENCY rule (design constraint; strengthens ASM-0808 item (1) from a claims rule to a dependency rule, per the review's ranked concern 3). Every Programme-3 experiment stage whose store is ADDRESSED FROM NATURAL INPUT - verifier-loop NL legs, GNN retrieval from NL queries, KV rule-firing keyed from NL, constrained decoding over NL prompts, H-DD store reinjection on NL tasks, H-PS end-to-end runs - is BLOCKED by the NLB gate (P3-E-NLB-1 clearing 0.90 retention + the S2 dangerous-wrong fail-closed criterion per vertical), OR runs on ORACLE inputs (gold parses / gold subgraphs / gold record addresses) and is labelled 'oracle-diagnostic' in its prereg, licensing NO W1 claim and no real-input claim of any kind. Additionally: (a) P3-D-NLB is itself blocked by the semantic-parsing / program-synthesis / selective-prediction literature review P3-LR-PARSE - the measured parser failure (l3a-parse 47.6 percent retention; a5-nl 41.6 percent + S2 kill fired) is not to be re-attempted with the same approach blind; (b) P3-E-NLB-1, coverage censuses, and G1 computations do NOT wait for index calibration (P3-E-CAL) - they make no index claim and gate everything else.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/programme-3-neurosymbolic-architecture.md sections 0, 3.3a, 4, 5; poc/gpt56-review/p3-review-20260711/review.md sections 'Honesty and programme risks' (NL wall not encoded in dependencies) + section 3 (sequencing) + ranked concern 3", "rationale": "The review showed revision 1 acknowledged the NL wall rhetorically but let GNN retrieval, KV rules, constrained decoding, and H-DD reinjection reach Phase-2 without demonstrated query-to-symbol grounding. The wall is now encoded as blocking edges in the WBS, with the oracle-diagnostic label as the only alternative path, and the parser redesign is lit-review-gated so the measured failure is not repeated.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "MEASURED basis restated within envelopes: l3a-parse FAIL (safe) and a5-nl FAIL (dangerous, S2 fired). The N=2 redesign-cycle bound on NLB attempts lives in K-P3v2(2) (ASM-0818)."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:218:{"id": "ASM-0817", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "Programme-3 gate ladder (design choice; supersedes-in-part ASM-0803's rung-only progression). Every family progresses through five INFORMATION-GAINING GATES, cheapest first, so failures localise: G1 coverage-ceiling - compute Delta_max <= sum_b w_b * kappa_b * (1 - a_b_cov) (w_b = index weight, kappa_b = store-covered fraction of benchmark b's items, a_b_cov = baseline accuracy on covered items); if even perfect covered-item correction cannot reach delta_k the index-mover claim is killed on paper, no GPU (mandatory first step for H-VL, H-RULE, and store-side H-DD; computed in P3-D-POWER). G2 oracle-interface - with gold parses/subgraphs/record addresses, does the mechanism help at all (oracle-diagnostic label, no W1 claim, per ASM-0814); a G2 fail localises to the mechanism. G3 boundary-degradation - how much of G2 survives realistic NL mapping through the NLB-gated front-end, with the P3-D-ORACLE decomposition attributing the loss across parse / retrieval-addressing / execution / generation; a G3 fail localises to the boundary. G4 full-system-vs-frontier - the W1 attempt against F(B_k) with the full framework + sealed eval. G5 scaling - the W1 margin held or improved across >= 2 sizes. Compute rungs R-0..R-4 remain as compute HOMES; promotion requires the current gate's pre-registered primary; a family failing the SAME gate at two consecutive rungs (or failing G1/G2 outright) is closed at scope. SEQUENCING: P3-E-NLB-1, coverage censuses, and G1 computations do not wait for P3-E-CAL; every G4 experiment requires the frozen KOT-FAIR/2 + P3-E-CAL PASS + the G4 block (P3-D-THREAT, P3-D-BASE, P3-D-FRONTIER, P3-D-HW, P3-D-RAGC). W2-CONDITIONALITY (fixing the review-flagged inconsistency): the W2 Pareto sweep inside P3-E-SCALE-2 runs ONLY conditional on W1 passing at R-2; any compression curve produced before a W1 PASS is labelled DIAGNOSTIC, never W2.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/programme-3-neurosymbolic-architecture.md sections 1.4, 3.1, 4; poc/gpt56-review/p3-review-20260711/review.md section 3 'Scaling ladder and cost approach'", "rationale": "The review showed the rung-only ladder lets an architecture fail ambiguously (graph encoder vs retrieval vs NL parse) and that the coverage bound is computable without GPU spend; the gate structure kills failures earlier, localises them, and encodes the review's sequencing corrections (NLB/coverage independent of calibration; W2 conditional on W1).", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Supersedes-in-part ASM-0803 (rung discipline and W2 timing); the rung table, compute homes, and promotion-spend gating in ASM-0803 stand. Given measured external coverage (~0 on external censuses; m0b 0.3542 friendliest-corpus), G1 is expected to bind hard and early - that is its purpose."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:220:{"id": "ASM-0819", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "Programme-3 revision-2 work-breakdown structure (process decision; supersedes ASM-0807). PHASE-0 = TEN literature reviews + one direct-design task, all parallel: P3-LR-EVAL (evaluation/AI-index methodology: HELM, composite-index statistics, contamination + sealed-eval practice, proxy-rung validity, benchmark floors/ceilings); P3-LR-SYS (lifecycle cost, MLPerf-style systems benchmarking, storage/I-O economics, energy measurement); P3-LR-RAG (RAG, structured retrieval, knowledge graphs, tool-using neural baselines, adaptive test-time compute); P3-LR-PARSE (semantic parsing, program synthesis, grammar induction, uncertainty/selective prediction); P3-LR-NTP (neural theorem proving, differentiable logic, neural algorithmic reasoning, proof-trace distillation); P3-LR-FUSE (GNN-LLM fusion + neurosymbolic integration survey; absorbs revision-1 P3-LR-NSA + P3-LR-GNN); P3-LR-RULE (rule-injection into transformers); P3-LR-SURG (model compression, dimension/structured pruning, distillation, the exact invariances of transformer model surgery / causal representation analysis); P3-LR-STORE (store authoring/maintenance/provenance + knowledge-update economics); P3-LR-TINY (tiny-model training + small-scale scaling laws); P3-MF-0 (measurement + fair-comparison framework draft). PHASE-1 adds the eight review-named design tasks alongside the family designs: P3-D-THREAT (formal resource/baseline threat model); P3-D-FRONTIER (neural frontier-builder optimising baselines per budget); P3-D-POWER (coverage x max-gain power analysis, the G1 instrument); P3-D-SEAL (independent sealed benchmark); P3-D-RAGC (matched generic-RAG control); P3-D-ORACLE (oracle-to-NL error decomposition); P3-D-HW (hardware repeatability + cold/warm-cache protocol); P3-D-LIFE (lifecycle cost amortisation); plus P3-D-INDEX, P3-D-BASE, P3-D-NLB (now blocked by P3-LR-PARSE), P3-D-PS (new family), P3-D-VL (blocked by P3-D-POWER), P3-D-GNN, P3-D-RULE, P3-D-DD, P3-D-GU. PHASE-2 blocking invariants: every G4/W1-relevant experiment is blocked by the G4 BLOCK = {P3-D-INDEX frozen, P3-D-THREAT, P3-D-BASE, P3-D-FRONTIER, P3-D-HW, P3-D-RAGC, P3-E-CAL PASS}; P3-E-NLB-1, coverage censuses/G1, and oracle-diagnostic G2 stages are EXEMPT from P3-E-CAL; every natural-input store-touching stage is blocked by P3-E-NLB-1 or runs oracle-labelled per ASM-0814; P3-E-DD-1 is blocked by P3-E-DD-0 PASS; P3-E-SCALE-2 requires >= 1 Phase-2 survivor + maintainer gate + the G4 block. Full dependency graph as drawn in the design document section 5. Nothing is created/frozen/run by the design document; the coordinator beads it.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/programme-3-neurosymbolic-architecture.md section 5; poc/gpt56-review/p3-review-20260711/review.md section 4 'Work breakdown'", "rationale": "The review required expanding the lit-review layer (RAG baselines, semantic parsing, theorem proving, model-surgery invariances, lifecycle/systems benchmarking, contamination/sealed-eval statistics, store economics) and named eight missing design tasks; the dependency graph now encodes the NL/coverage wall (ASM-0814), the gate ladder (ASM-0817), and the measurement-first invariant, so the coordinator can bead it directly.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Supersedes ASM-0807. Bead identifiers are design-document names; the coordinator assigns bd ids at creation."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:225:{"id": "ASM-0824", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "KOT-DECOMP/1 governance and gate feed (design choice; corrects the review's ranked concern 3 - the reviewed draft invented a FULL-REAL exemption class the design cannot grant itself). (1) sigma = gamma_G3 / gamma_G2 with gamma_G2 = gamma(G2-ANCHOR) and gamma_G3 = gamma(FULL-REAL) per ASM-0821, defined only when the one-sided 95 percent LCB of gamma_G2 > 0; K-P3v2(5)'s 'G2 gain fails to survive G3 at the pre-registered retention margin' is evaluated as UCB95(sigma) < sigma_min with sigma_min set in the family prereg. (2) THE BOUNDARY-DIAGNOSTIC EXEMPTION IS A PROPOSAL, NOT A GRANT: programme rev-2's sequencing exemptions name P3-E-NLB-1, the G1 censuses, and oracle-labelled G2 only; this entry REQUESTS a programme/ASM-0814 amendment creating a boundary-diagnostic class for FULL-REAL runs of this instrument (licensing only the measured retention/sigma/attribution vector - never an index, usefulness, or competitive claim) and bundles the P3-E-CAL sequencing exemption for decomposition runs into the same request; the request has NO EFFECT until an explicit coordinator/maintainer ratification decision is recorded as an amendment. FAIL-CLOSED MEANWHILE: (a) configurations in which every boundary-crossing store-addressing stage is oracled run now as ordinary oracle-diagnostic under ASM-0814; (b) FULL-REAL and partially-real-boundary cells are populated ONLY by replaying frozen, already-measured per-item artifacts of registered runs (no new natural-input execution); a missing artifact excludes that cell with disclosure and never triggers re-execution; (c) any new-family FULL-REAL leg waits for per-vertical NLB clearance or the ratified amendment. (3) KOT-DECOMP/1 SUPPLEMENTS KOT-FAIR/2: the attribution annex is a mandatory co-publication of every G4 attempt by a store-touching family, but it does NOT satisfy or replace KOT-FAIR/2's factorial content-type x retrieval-architecture x executor controls or the matched generic-RAG comparator - those remain separately mandatory. (4) Every configuration with >= 1 oracled stage stays oracle-diagnostic: no W1 claim, no real-input claim of any kind; no oracle number travels unlabelled (claims-lint pattern rider on the shakedown bead). (5) RESOURCE ACCOUNTING: actual CPU/GPU hours of ALL splice runs enter the family's tuning/development audit trail (KOT-FAIR/2 tuning-symmetry ledger); oracle authoring, dual annotation, adjudication, and K-phrasing production hours enter KOT-LIFE/1; any FULL-REAL figure feeding a G4 reading carries the complete KOT-COST/2 warm/cold resource vector, not only cost_us|tokens; 1-2B (R-3) decomposition reruns are explicitly budgeted in the family's R-3 prereg from the gated R-3 allocation, never absorbed silently.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/ORACLE.md sections 7.2, 9, 10; docs/next/programme-3-neurosymbolic-architecture.md lines 194-201 and 881-889 (ASM-0814/0817 exemption lists); poc/gpt56-review/rev-dORACLE-20260711/last-message.json ranked concern 3 + 'KOT-FAIR/2 and resources'", "rationale": "The reviewer showed the draft's boundary-diagnostic class conflicted with the programme rule that every natural-input store-touching leg is NLB-blocked or oracle-labelled, and that the design was granting itself the exemption; this entry converts the exemption into a ratification request with a fail-closed interim rule, and closes the review's resource-accounting gaps at the governance level.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Registers the reviewed draft's proposed ASM-ORC-5, restructured per the review. ASM-0814's W1 prohibition is not weakened anywhere; ratification is a coordinator/maintainer act, not this design's."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:237:{"id": "ASM-0884", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "G1 Delta_max validity preconditions (rev-dMF0 'G1 is not yet a genuinely cheap, decisive bound'): (1) per-benchmark HEADROOM clamp \u2014 Delta-tilde_max,b = min(kappa_b*(1-a_b_cov)/(ceiling_b-chance_b), 1-min(s-tilde_b_B,1)) so covered-item gain cannot exceed the clamped scalar's available headroom; (2) kappa_b=0 => Delta-tilde_max,b=0 with a_b_cov undefined-and-unused; (3) uncertainty by census mode \u2014 a complete finite census of a frozen suite has no counting uncertainty, a sampled census carries sampling error, an automated census carries measured classifier error; each propagates with a_b_cov estimation error to UCB95(Delta_max), and the kill compares UCB95(Delta_max) < delta_k; (4) coverage-label false-negative protection \u2014 'covered' = answerable-from-the-store; uncertain items count as COVERED, an automated labeller must have its false-negative rate measured on an adjudicated audit sample and folded into the upper bound on kappa_b, and the kappa adjudication protocol + inter-annotator agreement + human-hours accounting are frozen by P3-D-POWER BEFORE any G1 kill fires; (5) manual formalisation used to validate the labeller is an oracle diagnostic (ASM-0814 label) with logged human cost, never a capability input. Until (1)-(5) are frozen, G1 outputs are provisional and kill nothing.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/MF0.md section 9.4; poc/gpt56-review/rev-dMF0-20260711/last-message.json G1 item", "rationale": "The review found the draft-1 bound lacked the clamping/headroom term, left a_cov undefined at zero coverage, mis-assigned counting uncertainty to complete censuses, and above all ignored that coverage labels are semantic judgements whose false negatives shrink kappa and invalidate the UPPER bound; the kill instrument must err in the killed family's favour.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Registered by the MF0 draft-2 revision (GPT-5.6 review rev-dMF0-20260711 applied); fresh ASM-0880..0909 block, append-only. Renumbered twice pre-citation: three concurrent Phase-1 review-revision writers collided on the 0820 block and the FRONT/1 revision holds 0850+."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:245:{"id": "ASM-0860", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "P3-D-POWER corrected G1 bound + kill-soundness contract (supersedes-in-part the raw-scale Delta_max statement inside ASM-0817 and the unregistered in-doc proposals of POWER.md revision 1). The G1 ceiling is computed on the chance/ceiling-normalized KOT-AI-INDEX/2 scale over EVERY component of the frozen index pin: a censused, Form-A-eligible accuracy component contributes W_b*min(cap_b, kappa_b*(1-a_b_cov)/span_b); every uncensused component, every component whose metric has no registered max-gain functional, and every weighted domain with no enumerated components contributes its FULL HEADROOM (effectively kappa_UB=1, a_cov_LB=0, capped at the benchmark's normalized-score headroom cap_b) \u2014 no component is ever silently assigned zero possible gain. A missing covered-slice baseline is imputed the distribution-free lower bound a_cov=0 (never chance: below-chance baselines exist and deliberately wrong predictions are perfectly correctable). span_b is lower-bounded via the registered ceiling uncertainty. The kill quantity is a SIMULTANEOUS one-sided 95% upper bound: all stochastic intervals taken in one run share a Bonferroni-split alpha (each one-sided at 0.05/m), so by the union bound and monotonicity simUCB95(Delta_max)=sum of per-term UBs is a valid family-wise 95% upper bound; per-term unadjusted 95% bounds are NOT accepted as a joint bound. Kill iff simUCB95(Delta_max) < delta_k.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/POWER.md sections 1.2, 1.4, 3.1-3.3; poc/gpt56-review/rev-dPOWER-20260711/last-message.json blocking findings 1-3; docs/next/lit/EVAL.md section 5.3", "rationale": "The independent GPT-5.6 review demonstrated the revision-1 rig could issue FALSE KILLS three ways: censused-only summation silently assigned zero gain to every other index component; a_cov=chance imputation understates the ceiling (models can score below chance); and summing separate per-benchmark 95% Wilson bounds does not preserve 95% joint coverage. Each defect pushed Delta_max DOWN, violating the upper-bound direction the kill's soundness rests on. This contract restores the invariant that every approximation inflates Delta_max, making a fired kill sound.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Implemented in poc/p3-power/power.py (whole-index iteration, full-headroom imputation with flags, integer-count inputs, Bonferroni z via NormalDist.inv_cdf). The revision-1 live define-lane kill (0.0038 < 0.03) is WITHDRAWN under this contract; the corrected run reports simUCB95 ~ 0.81 ILLUSTRATIVE-ONLY."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:248:{"id": "ASM-0863", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "Abstention-scoring dependency edge (adopts round1-critique-synthesis section B.2.3 as a registered dependency). The firewall bound Form B \u2014 Delta_max^B = sum_b W_b_abstain * (share of baseline errors on b that are covered contradictions) * g_abstain \u2014 is UNCOMPUTABLE until P3-D-INDEX registers the abstention-scoring transform (the per-correct-abstention credit g_abstain). Therefore: any firewall/selective-mechanism family's G1 (Form B) and G4 are BLOCKED on that P3-D-INDEX decision; the P3-D-INDEX freeze must register abstention scoring BEFORE any selective-mechanism G1 or G4 prereg freezes; on an accuracy-only index Form B == 0 and the firewall's index-mover claim is dead by construction. The rig implements this as a fail-closed refusal (ERR_FORM_B_UNREGISTERED), never as a silent Form-A fallback.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/POWER.md section 1.3; docs/next/arch/round1-critique-synthesis.md sections A.3, B.2.3; docs/next/lit/EVAL.md section 8 open question 1", "rationale": "A pure claim-firewall cannot add correct answers; its index gain exists only under a scoring rule that credits correct abstention, which is an open normative P3-D-INDEX choice. Computing Form B under a guessed credit would smuggle an unregistered scoring decision into a kill/survive verdict; refusing until the transform is registered keeps the dependency explicit and auditable.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "The existing P3-D-FIREWALL bead carries the design work; this ASM is the registered edge. power.py --form B exits 2 with ERR_FORM_B_UNREGISTERED."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:249:{"id": "ASM-0864", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "The P3-D-POWER G1 decision rule, verbatim (POWER.md section 4). Step 0 VERDICT ELIGIBILITY (all required, else the run is ILLUSTRATIVE-ONLY and emits NO verdict): frozen index pin (frozen:true); complete census pin block (model_checkpoint, harness_hash, prompt_policy, seeds, store_hash, kernel_hash, world_layer_hash, mapper_hash, grammar_version, benchmark_revisions); declared coverage_lane and census_mode with label_fn_ub or a registered sampling frame; a registered Form-A family-eligibility reference (or, for Form B, a registered abstention-scoring transform). Steps 1-3: read kappa from the oracle-coverage census and integer correct_cov/n_cov baselines; compute simUCB95(Delta_max) per the ASM-0820 contract over the WHOLE index, scalar and per-domain; KILL the index-mover claim for family F at rung k iff simUCB95(Delta_max^F) < delta_k (domain-scoped: iff simUCB95 < delta_k^d for every store-touched domain, that domain fully censused). Step 4: mapper-parse-lane kills are CONTINGENT on the oracle census; oracle/upper-sieve kills are UNCONDITIONAL. Step 5 LICENSING: the bound is an oracle-diagnostic (ASM-0814 sense) \u2014 a kill licenses only 'no mechanism can move the index-mover claim for F at rung k by delta_k on this suite', makes no W1 claim, and does not touch F's value as a scoped instrument; SURVIVAL licenses nothing except proceeding to G2 and to sizing. The G4 primary the sizing bead must implement is LCB95(INDEX(S)-INDEX(C)) > delta_k with FWER control across the F(B_k) comparator set and a hierarchical paired bootstrap over items/prompts/seeds (suite never resampled as a benchmark-universe sample); sizing requires paired outcome variance/correlation, prompt and seed variance components, comparator multiplicity, and the exact bootstrap hierarchy \u2014 counts plus Delta are insufficient, and no G4 prereg may cite a sample size before the P3-D-POWER-SIZE rig exists and is calibrated.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/POWER.md sections 4, 5; docs/next/programme-3-neurosymbolic-architecture.md sections 2.5, 7.1; poc/gpt56-review/rev-dPOWER-20260711/last-message.json (verdict + 'sizing deliverable is not implemented')", "rationale": "The review required withdrawing the 'complete/runnable G1 deliverable' language and gating any real kill on the frozen pin, complete census pins, eligibility registration, and a sound statistical construction; and it found the sizing half was a sketch misdescribed as implemented. Registering the rule verbatim with an explicit eligibility step makes the kill mechanically auditable and prevents a rerun of the withdrawn revision-1 kill; registering the sizing requirements prevents a G4 prereg citing sizes the rig cannot yet compute.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Adjudicates programme kill K-P3v2(1) (ASM-0818): the completeness rule cuts both ways \u2014 K-P3v2(1) cannot fire off a partial census either. Sizing implementation is the proposed P3-D-POWER-SIZE bead."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:250:{"id": "ASM-0865", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "P3-D-POWER census/rung pin schema and KOT-FAIR/2 resource accounting. (1) PIN: a verdict-eligible census input must carry the full pin block {model_checkpoint, harness_hash, prompt_policy, seeds, store_hash, kernel_hash, world_layer_hash, mapper_hash, grammar_version, benchmark_revisions} plus enforced enums coverage_lane in {mapper-parse, oracle, upper-sieve} and census_mode in {exhaustive, sampled}; a free-text rung string is not a pin. No cross-rung, cross-store, or cross-suite reuse of a census or Delta_max verdict unless every pin field matches; any store/kernel hash change invalidates kappa. (2) RESOURCE ACCOUNTING: coverage is store-version- and budget-dependent, so a G1 run pins the canonically packed store/kernel artifacts (the rig echoes the hashes into its output) and the programme distinguishes three ceilings: (a) Delta_max under the current admissible B_k store (the measured computation); (b) Delta_max under a preregistered maximum store-growth envelope (an input scenario, always labelled, never a measurement); (c) the cost of reaching kappa* \u2014 bytes, authoring/review/indexing human-hours, and B_k admissibility under KOT-LIFE/1. A naked kappa* value is NOT an actionable coverage target: the ingestion plan must attach (c) before kappa* is cited in any prereg, and the rig prints this restriction on every output.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/POWER.md sections 2.2, 3.5; poc/gpt56-review/rev-dPOWER-20260711/last-message.json ('The 100M-2B pinning is incomplete' + 'KOT-FAIR/2 and resource accounting')", "rationale": "The review showed the revision-1 input schema carried only a free-text rung and lacked checkpoint/harness/prompt/seed/store hashes and metric typing, making cross-rung reuse unsafe, and that kappa* was presented without bytes, construction cost, or B_k admissibility. Pinning the full tuple and splitting the three ceilings keeps every coverage number attached to the exact artifacts and budget it was measured under.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Implemented as verdict_eligibility() + CENSUS_PIN_FIELDS in power.py; store-pin echo rides the JSON output. Fresh block 0820-0849 opened for P3-D-POWER revision 2; 0826-0849 remain free."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:258:{"id": "ASM-0920", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "P3-D-RAGC contract and scope: the matched generic-RAG/tool-use control is a CLOSED, NAMED arm inventory -- GR-A shared/matched generic-RAG (BM25+dense sub-cells; REQUIRED F(B_k) member and primary attribution control whenever S uses a store), GR-B native generic-RAG (additional frontier point), GR-C generic tool-use/generic-executor, GR-D matched retry/search with a generic acceptance signal, R0 retrieval-off floor -- plus perturbation cells PS (position-shuffle), RD (random-document, control-only), OR (oracle-retrieval, oracle-diagnostic only, never F(B_k), no W1 claim). Every consuming prereg names instantiated arms/cells with per-cell discrimination claims and claim licences. Gate placement: parity diagnostics feed G1 (census-class, P3-E-CAL-exempt); OR is G2 oracle-diagnostic; the GR set is mandatory at every store-touching G4/W1 experiment. The control consumes natural benchmark text natively and is NEVER NLB-gated. Generators are the rung anchors pinned by P3-D-BASE across the 100M-2B span.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/RAGC.md sections 0-1; executes ASM-0812 cell (f) + ASM-0890/0891; inherits ASM-0808/0814/0817 discipline", "rationale": "The f2b assessment shows the one audited end-task sign is consistent with aligned-answer-key+retry and had no generic-RAG arm; a single vague 'RAG baseline' cannot decompose a win, so the control must be a closed inventory of named arms each isolating one axis, with the oracle and NL-integrity rules preventing the control from being weakened to share the kernel's measured NL wall.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Block ASM-0920-0939 assigned to P3-D-RAGC (bead kernel-of-truth-s55r.15); 0928-0939 remain free."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:259:{"id": "ASM-0921", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "RAGC Rule-1 execution (source-content derivation + information parity): one pinned derivation matrix D per vertical -- kernel records via the standing mint pipeline version; passages via a pinned chunker (proposed 256-token/stride-128, sentence-snapped; params tunable on dev within the arm's T_k meter, then pinned); triples via deterministic extraction where structure permits (the measured a5 route) else one pinned open IE extractor; tool schemas via a deterministic schema-to-function generator. Byte-cap parity: each arm's packed indexed objects + index + embedder + executor bytes <= the same store_bytes(B_k), measured by the one canonical packing script; slack may not be banked. Information parity beyond FRONT/1's four checks is MEASURED, not certified, by two pre-registered diagnostics: P5 decisive-span coverage per arm (blind power-sized annotation; per-arm kappa vector, doubling as the G1 census input) and P6 oracle-delivery answerable-fraction probe (oracle-diagnostic). A pinned parity band eps_par (proposed 0.05 absolute on kappa) applies fail-closed: out-of-band comparisons have their attribution sentence DOWNGRADED to 'confounded by derivation coverage' while frontier membership survives.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/RAGC.md section 2; inherits ASM-0853 Rule 1 verbatim", "rationale": "The RAG lit-review found no published precedent for cross-representation information parity; certifying it is impossible (different object types change the retrieval problem), so the honest executable form is equal snapshot + equal byte cap + equal metered derivation effort + measured coverage/consumption diagnostics with a pre-registered downgrade rule instead of a silent pass.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "P5 annotation is costed work (power-sized by P3-D-POWER), not ~$0 CPU, per the round-1 census-accounting correction."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:282:{"id": "ASM-0980", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "NTP-GATE interface operationalisation (design choice). The gate operationalises the two NTP-dependent interfaces as: (1) CONTINUATION SET := for a partial kot-query/1 query under the closed grammar in the pinned field order (relational ops: rel->direction->subject->qualifier; instance: entity->concept; define: subject), the per-field admissible-value sets at two grades - G1 = the licensed vocabulary for the next field (engine index read), G2 = the values for which SOME completion of the remaining fields yields status=answer (exists-completion semantics); (2) REPLAYABLE DERIVATION TRACE := an emitted certificate is CLOSED iff a store restricted to exactly the records it names (provenance world-record ids + license axiom files) reproduces the same answer value under the same query; refusals, which carry no record references, have no certificate by construction. A PASS/FAIL on any stronger trace notion (multi-step proof objects, search transitions) is out of scope until a consuming arm registers a stronger contract: this v0 engine is a depth-1 deterministic lookup oracle with a pre-registered validation order, so its complete derivation IS the validation-step-plus-consulted-records sequence.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/NTP-GATE.md sections 2, 4; docs/next/lit/NTP.md section 8 (oracle/API gate); tools/axiom/kot_axiom.py (query validation order)", "rationale": "These are the weakest interfaces the dependent architectures actually consume: P3/H-RULE-CD masks need exactly the admissible-continuation sets (G2 is the mask; G1 is its cheap over-approximation); P6/H-GU proof-trace curricula and the verifier-loop's audit story need self-contained derivations, for which replay-closure is the mechanical test; H-VL retry needs named machine-readable diagnostics. Operationalising the gate at the consuming-arm interface (not at a theorem-prover trace ideal the engine was never specified to have) is what makes the gate decision-relevant and cheaply falsifiable.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Fresh block ASM-0980-0999 opened for the NTP oracle/API gate (P3-E-NTP-GATE-0 precursor); 0983-0999 remain free. Registered by docs/next/design/NTP-GATE.md."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:284:{"id": "ASM-0982", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "NTP-GATE build spec and acceptance criteria (design choice). The emission surface the dependent arms need is completed by three additive, CPU-only, opt-in engine extensions, none of which may alter the default query() emission bytes (the l3a/a5 frozen instruments consume that surface): B1 TRACE EMISSION - query(q, trace=True) adds a trace field: the ordered validation-step sequence with, per step, the outcome and every consulted record reference (axiom constraint refs, world-record ids INCLUDING licensing-support class assertions, inverseOf canonicalisation flips, definitional provenance plus the mint-bridge entries consulted); B2 CONTINUATION API - continuations(partial) returns the ASM-0980 G1/G2 per-field sets, computed from the engine's indexes analytically, with the probe's brute-force adapter as the frozen reference semantics (equivalence tested); B3 STRUCTURED REFUSAL DIAGNOSTICS - refusals gain a machine-readable diagnostic block naming the terminating validation step and, for ERR_CONFLICT, stable references into the store-violation objects. ACCEPTANCE (mechanical, all required): (a) replay closure 100 percent - the probe's certificate-replay leg, re-run consuming trace-named record sets, yields outcome=exact for every covered answer in both pinned eval sets (baseline measured 464/600 and 438/855 on license+provenance alone); (b) adapter equivalence - B2 output equals the reference adapter's G1/G2 sets on all worked partials; (c) byte-identical default - both frozen instruments' full eval passes are byte-identical pre/post build; (d) determinism - doubled-pass identity on all new surfaces. Estimated cost: ~330-550 added engine/test lines, zero GPU, no schema version change to existing emissions.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/NTP-GATE.md section 5; poc/ntp-gate/probe.py (reference adapter + replay leg)", "rationale": "The probe measured exactly which records the current certificate omits (licensing-support class assertions; the class-licensing axiom behind instance-true's asserted license; all refusal context), so the build is a bounded engineering task, not research; making the probe's replay leg the acceptance test converts the NTP section 8 blocking requirement from an assertion into a mechanical gate.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Registered by docs/next/design/NTP-GATE.md."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:285:{"id": "ASM-0960", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "P3-E-DECONF-0 contract and scope: the aligned-generic-store deconfound decomposes along the measured f2b mechanism into a RUNTIME channel (store acts only through the deterministic check() accept seam; owned by this experiment) and an AUTHORED-CONTENT channel (store content reaches the model through regenerated surfaces; owned by knull/knull-v2, untouched). Stage inventory: A1 aligned-generic-answer-key extensional-equivalence audit (CPU, ~USD 0, G1-class census); A2 generic-typed-store + generic-executor reproduction of the a5-llm engine leg (CPU, ~USD 0, GR-C precursor); B strong generic tool/RAG baseline through the identical verify-retry topology on the externally-adjudicated d-qa-t eval prefix (single small GPU run, G2-class attribution). No cell is a W1 claim; nothing is NLB-gated (no natural-language input exists in the design); DECONF amends no frozen record, verdict, audit, or ruling (f2b-replicate, f2b-transfer, knull, knull-v2 all stand byte-identical); DECONF cells are right-sized PRECURSORS of the RAGC manifest cells and are superseded by them for any G4/W1 use.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/DECONF.md sections 0 and 7; executes round1-steering recommended kill (b); relation map to MF0 section 8.5 cell (e) (ASM-0891), RAGC arms (ASM-0920/0924), FRONT rules (ASM-0853)", "rationale": "Both round-1 subjective analyses independently named the aligned-generic-store deconfound the highest-value early experiment against the programme's single biggest risk (attribution collapse); splitting it where the measured mechanism splits it makes the decisive half runnable now at ~USD 0 without waiting on the knull quality-gate rewrite, the human-annotation queue, or the RAGC/FRONT scaffolding the steering froze.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Block ASM-0960-0979 assigned to this bead; 0967-0979 remain free. External GPT-5.6-class review precedes any prereg freeze."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:292:{"id": "ASM-1000", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "P3-D-CODEVERT contract and licence space: CODEVERT/1 is the critique+synthesis of GPT-5.6's CASK-CODE/1 code-vertical selective-coprocessor proposal (poc/gpt56-review/arch-codevert-20260711/last-message.json). Its entire licence space is an ARCHITECTURE-FAMILY claim (calibrated contract front-end + evidence-gated ambiguity-set execution + exact deterministic substrate vs matched RAG/tool baselines at equal risk and resources, on the code vertical) - never a kernel-CONTENT claim in either direction: nothing in the v1 design consumes NSM semantics, explications, or the encoder (the a5 world is structural-not-NSM per ASM-0007), so kernel-content value remains owned by knull-v2 / A-F0 / the f2b-transfer line regardless of any CODEVERT outcome. The instance-of(symbol, concept) query family is retained with its own stratum as the single seam where kernel concept content could later enter; no G1-G5 rung claims it. Steering-freeze compliance: G4/G5 receive no further design spend until G2 reads out.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/CODEVERT.md sections 0, 5, 10; round1-steering.md convergence item 6; registry/assessments/a5-llm.json does_not_license; ASM-0007", "rationale": "Both round-1 subjective analyses named the code-vertical selective coprocessor the single most promising direction; the critique's load-bearing addition is that even a full win here is kernel-free, so the claim scope must be pinned before any experiment exists to prevent a later architecture win being narrated as kernel-content evidence.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Block ASM-1000-1029 assigned to this bead, disjoint from all prior blocks (highest prior id ASM-0982); entries 1009-1029 remain free. External GPT-5.6-class review precedes any commit/prereg use."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:296:{"id": "ASM-1004", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "G1 real-repo extraction census (the cheapest falsifier, ~USD 0 CPU + minimal annotation): a repo-selection rule pinned BEFORE inspection (20-30 permissively-licensed Python repos in a pinned size band, disjoint from all front-end training/calibration material); run the extractor; report per-relation fact counts by status and kappa_q = the fraction of a mechanically-enumerated query census (all eight families over extracted symbols) whose answers are fully proved; blind two-annotator precision check on a ~150-fact sample. Kill floor (planning values, maintainer-adjustable at prereg): kappa_q < 0.5 on the pinned pool, or blind extractor precision < 0.95, kills the full-distribution product claim before any model is trained; the direction then survives only re-scoped as a covered-slice tool. G1 precedes all task authoring and all model work.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/CODEVERT.md section 7 G1; coverage-wall record: registry/verdicts/g8.json 0/1000 + registry/verdicts/m0b.json 0.3542 per ASM-0001", "rationale": "The programme's measured existential risk is coverage; CASK-CODE/1 authored evaluation material before measuring real-repo extraction coverage anywhere - the census is cheaper than the pilot and can kill the product claim outright, so it goes first.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": ""}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:300:{"id": "ASM-1008", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "Forward expectation (never a premise): real-repo extraction coverage kappa_q will clear the G1 floor (Python relational facts being a far friendlier extraction target than the measured g8/m0b coverage walls), and the NLB-FE/1 recipe with evidence-gated ambiguity sets will clear the G2 screen bars (0.80 completed coverage at <= 1 percent point dangerous error; +5 points set-over-top1; correct-DSL-in-set miss <= 10 percent).", "backing_ref": "", "rationale": "Registers the direction's optimism where the register can watch it die: the closest published numbers (110M whole-frame 88.2 ATIS; TeCoD 83.6-89.2) sit at or below the interesting bars, and no cited work reports retention-at-S2-bound for a <= 360M parser on a comparable grammar.", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "resolution_path": "Resolved directly by P3-E-CODEVERT-G1 (kappa_q census, ~USD 0) and P3-E-CODEVERT-G2 (merged pilot, <= 5 GPU-h + ~USD 25); no decision may premise on this entry while open.", "notes": "Non-load-bearing counterpart of the ASM-1004/1005 kill floors."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:301:{"id": "ASM-1010", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "A1 licence narrowing: A1 is an executable equivalence/regression certificate over an exact projection of kernel-authored answer strings \u2014 not a test of independently-generic content, not G1; C_dec = 1.0 reads as structural-field runtime-inertness at the pinned scope (never 'kernel content is generic'); C_dec < 1.0 triggers the four-step implementation-cause triage ladder (projection bug / incomplete read-set / init-order / schema) before any semantic-candidate label; the \u00a71 invariance lemma is scoped to pinned harness/checker/output-space/init/store hashes; R-1/135M context only, no extrapolation to 100M\u20132B.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/DECONF.md \u00a71, \u00a73.0, \u00a73.2", "rationale": "Answers the review that A1 was overstated as a falsifiable test of independently-generic content and mislabelled G1; narrows it to an equivalence/regression certificate with an implementation-cause triage and a hash-scoped invariance lemma.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "registered from DECONF.md rev-B review-gate revision; amends ASM-0962"}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:305:{"id": "ASM-1014", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "KOT-FAIR slotting + NL wording correction: A1/A2 = pre-ladder CPU attribution diagnostics (not G1); Stage B = formal/oracle-addressed covered-slice G2 diagnostic (not W1/G4); BM25-only = cheap lexical precursor, never 'strong generic RAG baseline'; Stage B contains English and is NLB-exempt by evidence class, not by NL absence.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/DECONF.md \u00a70, \u00a72.3, \u00a75.3, \u00a77.2", "rationale": "Corrects the mislabelled KOT-FAIR/2 slotting (A1/A2/B were called G1/W1/G4), the 'strong baseline' overclaim on BM25-only, and the NL-discipline wording at the two flagged spots.", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "registered from DECONF.md rev-B review-gate revision; amends ASM-0960/0964/0965"}
